Okay.

15:09.800 --> 15:13.300
I read up and researched, and I moved us all, especially on PBS,

15:13.640 --> 15:17.500
not long ago, on that you hosted on Puppetry.

15:18.120 --> 15:20.720
And it went into how you all produced the show and everything.

15:20.900 --> 15:24.960
But could you give a little bit of a sort of visual explanation

15:24.960 --> 15:26.780
of what it's like on the set?

15:27.900 --> 15:33.200
Well, let's see. Because we were operating most of these characters from below,

15:33.960 --> 15:37.920
the sets were all built about four feet off the floor.

15:40.220 --> 15:42.220
And we would be operating

15:42.220 --> 15:46.140
with a...or sometimes through holes

15:46.140 --> 15:49.420
on the floor, or sometimes the character would be there.

15:49.860 --> 15:53.640
And there would be several people around

15:54.420 --> 15:57.520
operating cables going to one particular character.

15:58.520 --> 16:02.160
If you saw the credits on ET, so how many people

16:02.160 --> 16:05.820
were credited with operating ET. And we had

16:05.820 --> 16:09.140
dozens of characters that were all about that complicated.

16:09.780 --> 16:14.420
So you could imagine we would have lots and lots of performers.

16:15.220 --> 16:18.060
And we were always using a video system

16:18.060 --> 16:20.800
up through the last television camera.

16:21.700 --> 16:24.900
So we would be operating with television monitors.

16:26.020 --> 16:28.680
If I was inside of a character operating,

16:29.460 --> 16:32.280
I would be wearing a television monitor on my chest.

16:33.100 --> 16:36.680
And all the other people who were helping to operate that same character

16:36.680 --> 16:39.400
would also be watching television monitors.

16:39.400 --> 16:43.780
So it was that kind of a

16:43.780 --> 16:44.920
process.

16:48.920 --> 16:51.700
That sort of high tech

16:51.700 --> 16:54.820
industry. Yes, yes.

16:55.140 --> 16:59.500
We were using a lot of different kinds of technical

16:59.500 --> 17:02.520
and special effect.

17:03.240 --> 17:07.280
Mechanisms, radio control, marionette rigs,

17:07.280 --> 17:10.100
all of these things. But basically they're all

17:11.660 --> 17:14.880
ways of assisting the performer create a

17:14.880 --> 17:18.920
performance. So despite the fact that it's high tech,

17:19.680 --> 17:21.400
I really think of it as

17:24.220 --> 17:26.380
assisting a performance to happen.

17:26.780 --> 17:30.920
Because that is what everything revolves around.

17:31.880 --> 17:33.720
And the quality of the performance itself.

17:37.740 --> 17:39.660
Yes, that's very good. Very good explanation.

